The Financial Aid Office offers a one time computer loan for up to $1900 for qualifying UC Davis undergraduate students or $2000 for graduate students. To apply for the undergraduate or graduate computer loan, complete the application found http://financialaid.ucdavis.edu/undergraduate/students/computers.html here for undergraduates or http://financialaid.ucdavis.edu/graduate/Forms/gradforms3.html here for graduate students and attach a copy of the listed price of the computer of your choosing. You may turn in the completed application with the attached price estimate online in a single combined .pdf at the financial aid https://financialaid.ucdavis.edu/ContactUs/ contact page or at your respective financial aid desk at Dutton Hall. Keep in mind that it may take about month or longer to process your computer loan application.

More details can be found at their http://financialaid.ucdavis.edu/undergraduate/students/computers.html Undergraduate Computer Purchase Policy web page.

